        "id": "20_support_&_help_09_bug_reporting_md",
        "title": "Bug Reporting",
        "filename": "09 Bug Reporting.md",
        "rel_path": "20 Support & Help/09 Bug Reporting.md",
        "content": "# Bug Reporting\n\n## Purpose\nThis document defines the process for reporting and handling bugs on BlicBloc.\n\n## Bug Reporting Philosophy\n\n- **User-Friendly**: Easy for users to report\n- **Detailed**: Get detailed information\n- **Responsive**: Fast response to reports\n- **Transparent**: Keep users informed\n- **Efficient**: Efficient bug handling\n\n## Bug Reporting Process\n\n### User Flow\n\n| Step | Description | Owner |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| **1. Discover** | User discovers bug | User |\n| **2. Report** | User reports bug | User |\n| **3. Acknowledge** | Acknowledge report | Support |\n| **4. Investigate** | Investigate bug | Engineering |\n| **5. Fix** | Fix bug | Engineering |\n| **6. Deploy** | Deploy fix | Engineering |\n| **7. Notify** | Notify user | Support |\n\n### Reporting Channels\n\n| Channel | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Support Email** | Email bug reports |\n| **Help Center** | Bug report form (future) |\n| **In-App** | In-app reporting (future) |\n| **Social Media** | Social media reports |\n\n## Bug Report Form\n\n### Required Information\n\n| Field | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| **Summary** | Brief summary of issue |\n| **Description** | Detailed description |\n| **Steps to Reproduce** | Step-by-step instructions |\n| **Expected Behavior** | What should happen |\n| **Actual Behavior** | What actually happens |\n| **Screenshots** | Visual evidence |\n| **Device** | Device and browser |\n| **Account** | User account info |\n\n### Optional Information\n\n| Field | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| **Frequency** | How often it occurs |\n| **Severity** | User-reported severity |\n| **Workaround** | Is there a workaround? |\n| **Video** | Video recording |\n\n### Form Design\n\n| Element | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Clear Labels** | Clear field labels |\n| **Required Fields** | Mark required fields |\n| **Help Text** | Helpful instructions |\n| **Validation** | Validate input |\n| **Submit** | Submit button |\n\n## Bug Categories\n\n### Severity Levels\n\n| Level | Description | Example |\n|-------|-------------|---------|\n| **Critical** | Platform down, data loss | Can't log in, data corrupted |\n| **High** | Major feature broken | Can't publish, saving fails |\n| **Medium** | Minor feature broken | UI issue, formatting issue |\n| **Low** | Cosmetic issue | Typo, alignment issue |\n\n### Bug Types\n\n| Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| **Functional** | Feature doesn't work |\n| **UI/UX** | Design or usability issue |\n| **Performance** | Slow loading, lag |\n| **Security** | Security vulnerability |\n| **Compatibility** | Browser or device issue |\n\n## Bug Handling\n\n### Triage Process\n\n| Step | Description | Owner |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| **1. Receive** | Receive bug report | Support |\n| **2. Categorize** | Categorize bug | Support |\n| **3. Prioritize** | Set priority | Support |\n| **4. Assign** | Assign to engineer | Engineering |\n| **5. Track** | Track in system | Engineering |\n\n### Bug Priority Matrix\n\n| Impact | Frequency | Priority |\n|--------|-----------|----------|\n| **High** | Always | Critical |\n| **High** | Often | High |\n| **Medium** | Always | High |\n| **Medium** | Often | Medium |\n| **Low** | Always | Medium |\n| **Low** | Often | Low |\n\n### Bug Workflow\n\n| State | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| **Open** | Bug reported |\n| **In Progress** | Being worked on |\n| **Review** | Ready for review |\n| **Fixed** | Bug fixed |\n| **Closed** | Bug closed |\n| **Won't Fix** | Won't be fixed |\n\n## Bug Tracking\n\n### Tracking System\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Bug ID** | Unique bug identifier |\n| **Status** | Current status |\n| **Priority** | Priority level |\n| **Assignee** | Assigned to |\n| **Timeline** | Timeline of updates |\n| **History** | All updates |\n\n### Bug Reports\n\n| Report | Description | Frequency |\n|--------|-------------|-----------|\n| **Open Bugs** | All open bugs | Daily |\n| **Fixed Bugs** | Recently fixed | Daily |\n| **Bug Trends** | Trends over time | Weekly |\n| **Bug Summary** | Summary report | Monthly |\n\n## Bug Fix Process\n\n### Fix Steps\n\n| Step | Description | Owner |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| **1. Reproduce** | Reproduce bug | Engineering |\n| **2. Diagnose** | Find root cause | Engineering |\n| **3. Fix** | Implement fix | Engineering |\n| **4. Test** | Test fix | Engineering |\n| **5. Review** | Review code | Engineering |\n| **6. Deploy** | Deploy fix | Engineering |\n\n### Testing\n\n| Test Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| **Unit Testing** | Test individual components |\n| **Integration** | Test integration |\n| **Regression** | Test for regressions |\n| **User Acceptance** | User testing |\n\n## Bug Communication\n\n### User Communication\n\n| Update | Description | Timeline |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| **Acknowledgment** | Bug received | Immediate |\n| **Update** | Progress update | Weekly |\n| **Fix Notification** | Bug fixed | When fixed |\n| **Closure** | Issue closed | When closed |\n\n### Internal Communication\n\n| Update | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **Bug Report** | Internal bug report |\n| **Priority** | Priority assignment |\n| **Status Updates** | Regular updates |\n| **Release Notes** | Bug fixes included |\n\n## Bug Prevention\n\n### Prevention Strategies\n\n| Strategy | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| **Code Reviews** | Review code before merge |\n| **Testing** | Comprehensive testing |\n| **QA** | Quality assurance |\n| **Monitoring** | Monitor production |\n| **User Feedback** | Learn from feedback |\n\n### Quality Standards\n\n| Standard | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| **Code Quality** | Clean, maintainable code |\n| **Test Coverage** | High test coverage |\n| **Performance** | Performance standards |\n| **Security** | Security standards |\n\n## Success Metrics\n\n| Metric | Target |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Bug Detection** | 90%+ detected |\n| **Fix Time** | Under 7 days |\n| **Bug Recurrence** | < 5% |\n| **User Satisfaction** | 80%+ |\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. Create bug report form\n2. Set up bug tracking\n3. Define bug handling process\n4. Train team\n5. Launch bug reporting"
