        "content": "# Feature Requests\n\n## Purpose\nThis document defines the process for collecting, evaluating, and implementing feature requests.\n\n## Feature Request Philosophy\n\n- **User-Driven**: Users drive feature requests\n- **Collaborative**: Collaborative evaluation\n- **Transparent**: Transparent process\n- **Strategic**: Align with vision\n- **Impactful**: Focus on high-impact features\n\n## Feature Request Process\n\n### User Flow\n\n| Step | Description | Owner |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| **1. Idea** | User has feature idea | User |\n| **2. Submit** | User submits request | User |\n| **3. Review** | Review request | Product |\n| **4. Evaluate** | Evaluate request | Product |\n| **5. Plan** | Plan implementation | Product |\n| **6. Build** | Build feature | Engineering |\n| **7. Launch** | Launch feature | Product |\n\n### Submission Channels\n\n| Channel | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Support Email** | Email feature requests |\n| **Feedback Form** | In-app feedback |\n| **Help Center** | Feature request form |\n| **Social Media** | Social media requests |\n\n## Feature Request Form\n\n### Request Information\n\n| Field | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| **Feature** | Name of feature |\n| **Description** | Detailed description |\n| **Problem** | What problem does it solve? |\n| **Solution** | How should it work? |\n| **Priority** | How important is this? |\n| **Use Case** | How would you use it? |\n| **Alternatives** | Current workarounds |\n\n### Form Design\n\n| Element | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Clear Labels** | Clear field labels |\n| **Required Fields** | Mark required fields |\n| **Help Text** | Helpful instructions |\n| **Validation** | Validate input |\n| **Submit** | Submit button |\n\n## Feature Evaluation\n\n### Evaluation Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| **User Value** | Value to users |\n| **Business Value** | Value to business |\n| **Effort** | Development effort |\n| **Priority** | How urgent? |\n| **Strategic Fit** | Align with vision |\n| **Impact** | Impact on users |\n\n### Evaluation Process\n\n| Step | Description | Owner |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| **1. Initial Review** | Initial evaluation | Product |\n| **2. User Feedback** | Gather user feedback | Product |\n| **3. Feasibility** | Technical feasibility | Engineering |\n| **4. Prioritization** | Prioritize request | Product |\n| **5. Roadmap** | Add to roadmap | Product |\n\n### Scoring\n\n| Factor | Weight | Score |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| **User Value** | 5 | 1-5 |\n| **Business Value** | 4 | 1-5 |\n| **Strategic Fit** | 3 | 1-5 |\n| **Effort** | 3 | 1-5 |\n| **Priority** | 2 | 1-5 |\n\n## Feature Prioritization\n\n### Priority Levels\n\n| Level | Description | Timeline |\n|-------|-------------|----------|\n| **Critical** | Must have | Immediate |\n| **High** | Important | Next release |\n| **Medium** | Desirable | Future release |\n| **Low** | Nice to have | Long-term |\n| **Declined** | Won't implement | N/A |\n\n### Prioritization Factors\n\n| Factor | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **User Demand** | How many users want it? |\n| **Impact** | How much impact? |\n| **Effort** | How much work? |\n| **Risk** | How risky? |\n| **Timing** | When needed? |\n\n## Feature Roadmap\n\n### Roadmap Structure\n\n| Period | Features |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Now** | Current development |\n| **Next** | Next development |\n| **Future** | Future development |\n\n### Roadmap Communication\n\n| Communication | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| **User Updates** | Regular updates |\n| **Release Notes** | Feature announcements |\n| **Preview** | Feature previews |\n| **Feedback** | Collect feedback |\n\n## Feature Development\n\n### Development Process\n\n| Step | Description | Owner |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| **1. Design** | Design feature | Product |\n| **2. Develop** | Develop feature | Engineering |\n| **3. Test** | Test feature | QA |\n| **4. Launch** | Launch feature | Product |\n| **5. Monitor** | Monitor usage | Product |\n\n### User Testing\n\n| Test Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| **Alpha** | Internal testing |\n| **Beta** | Limited user testing |\n| **Public** | Public release |\n\n## Feature Communication\n\n### User Communication\n\n| Update | Description | Timeline |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| **Acknowledgment** | Request received | Immediate |\n| **Status** | Status update | Monthly |\n| **Development** | Development starts | When started |\n| **Launch** | Feature launched | When launched |\n\n### Communication Channels\n\n| Channel | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Email** | Email updates |\n| **Blog** | Blog posts |\n| **Social Media** | Social media |\n| **Release Notes** | Release notes |\n\n## Feature Tracking\n\n### Tracking System\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Request ID** | Unique identifier |\n| **Status** | Current status |\n| **Priority** | Priority level |\n| **Votes** | User votes |\n| **Updates** | Regular updates |\n\n### Feature Reports\n\n| Report | Description | Frequency |\n|--------|-------------|-----------|\n| **Top Requests** | Most requested | Weekly |\n| **Status** | Feature status | Monthly |\n| **Roadmap** | Roadmap updates | Quarterly |\n\n## Success Metrics\n\n| Metric | Target |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Feature Adoption** | 50%+ of users |\n| **User Satisfaction** | 80%+ |\n| **Feature Requests** | Monthly |\n| **Implementation Rate** | 20%+ |\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. Create feature request form\n2. Set up evaluation process\n3. Define prioritization\n4. Build roadmap\n5. Launch feature requests"
